Text to Number Transformation: Convert the Column Type

When you load data into a dataset, CRM Analytics tags a number (measure) column as text (a dimension) if it contains unexpected strings or characters. To perform a calculation on the column, such as calculating the average, use the Text To Number transformation.

During the column type conversion, the Text to Number transformation rounds decimals to the nearest whole number.

In the Transform node of a Data Prep recipe, select the text (dimension) column you want to convert to the Number (measure) column type.

To change more column attributes, click the Column Attributes box, change them, and click Apply.
